We offer competitive remuneration including career prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your portfolio and resume with current & expected salary by clicking 'Apply Now' for application.

(Data collected will only be used for job application processing. All related information will be kept up to 6 months and all personal data will be destroyed afterwards.)

Job Duties

Responsible for the whole set of video editing, motion graphic and infographic design for corporate video, animation and event promo.

Requirements

Certificate/Diploma/Degree holder in Creative Media, Multimedia Design, Motion Graphics or Animation;
Min 1 years solid experience in video motion graphic design with Premiere, After Effects, Illustrator, Photoshop;
3Ds Max knowledge is preferable;
Strong creative, presentation layout, visual design and video production artwork;
Able to work independently and under tight schedule;
Good communication & interpersonal skills;

Job Highlights 

Digital Media (DL.theVOC) + Technical Creative Projects + UI / UX Design

Good sense of art direction, graphic sense

Working with Award winning Creatives

Job Description: 

Provide full creative, design, project art direction and production support;

Responsible for social media OG design, GDN banner, graphics design, video editing, animation and other marketing materials;

Creating different designs for marketing use purpose in different platform such as desktop, mobile as well as kiosk;

Knowledge & experience in digital media industry is a plus; 

Requirements:

Diploma or above in Graphic / Multimedia / Web design or related fields;

Minimum 2 years’ relevant experience in graphic design, web design or advertising;

Photography and photo retouching, video post production, sound editing skills

Proficient in using PC / Mac Systems, Adobe Creative Cloud specifically Photoshop, Illustrator, Premiere, After Effects and other essential multimedia, interactive softwares, WordPress, Microsoft Office and other relevant software applications, familiar with HTML / HTML5 / CSS / JS is a plus;

Working knowledge of SEO best practice, GDN Display Ads, familiar with UI / UX design (Adobe XD, Figma, Sketch) is a big plus;

Strong multimedia and web sense and understanding of digital technology trends;

Creative, detail-oriented, enthusiastic, independent and self-motivated;

Good written and spoken in English and Chinese;

A perfect team player;

Portfolio attachment is a MUST;

Candidates with less experience would also be considered as Associate Art Director;

 Benefits:

Annual Leave

Birthday Leave

Performance Bonus

Medical Insurance

We offer 5–day work week, competitive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate. For interested parties please send a cover letter stating your current salary and expected salary with Resume, Graduation Certification and Transcript to us.

Candidates who are not contacted within 1 month from sending the resume should consider your applications filed for future opportunities. All applications will be treated in strict confidentiality and used for recruitment purpose only

