by e-mail to:  h r d _ h n @ h a r v e y n i c h o l s . c o m . h k
We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within eight weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months. A copy of our Personal Information Collection Statement will be provided upon request by contacting our Human Resources Division.

The Role
The Art Director is required to work hand-in-hand with Head of Marketing, primarily to generate the original idea, lead the art direction and present campaigns to top management, secondly to groom and coach the juniors, help manage the execution and production.

Responsibilities

Interpret a creative brief and turn it into a compelling story;
Produce innovative ideas for campaigns in line with the creative brief provided;
Translate marketing campaign ‘Big Idea’ into visual brand identity of our clients;
Produce key visuals for pitches and marketing campaign;
Translate a briefing into a visual statement using presentation tools such as PowerPoint, Google slide or Keynote;
Able to develop visual concepts which adhere to any brand style guideline and restrictions provided;
Work resourcefully, offer variety of alternative solutions to creative problems;
The ability to present your work clearly and confidently in front of internal stakeholders;
Hands-on working is needed, be ready to jump in with the highest level of design quality.

Requirements

Strong conceptual skills with a passion for big ideas;
Hungry to produce high quality work;
Solid technical art direction with a keen eye for detail;
Be interested in popular culture, social media and be up to date with current advertising trends and techniques;
Excellent command of English (native level would be an advantage) and Cantonese is required, both spoken and written;
Minimum 5 years of art directing and design work experience;
Ability to shift priorities and navigate between competing deadlines while managing multiple projects of varying sizes, topic and type;
Innovative, energetic and proactive, proven self-starter and a strong team player;
Exceptional art/design and verbal communication skills, presentation skills and organisational skills;
Regional experience is an advantage.

We offer the right candidate attractive remuneration package and outstanding prospects for career advancement and development.  The right candidate will progress career in a forward thinking and dynamic business with exciting growth plans.  If you are qualified and interested, please send your full resume with current & expected salary and availability by clicking "APPLY ".

All information collected will be treated as strictly confidential and used for recruitment purposes only. (Only shortlisted candidates will be notified)

