Casetify is looking for a Senior UXUI designer experienced in information architecture, interaction, and user testing to join our team. You will collaborate with the E-commerce team to design and build next generation Web/mobile applications. The right candidates will be excellent communicators, comfortable in a high-velocity startup, and passionate about creating products that transform people’s lifestyle.
Responsibilities:
Prepare UX/UI design and materials including wire framing, mockup and rapid prototyping for various interfaces, including websites, mobile devices and apps for ecommerce site;
Analyze current user journey to understand motivation, expose pain points, issues and improvement opportunities;
Conduct user research, A/B testing, and propose solutions to optimize customer experience;
Communicate concepts and work collaboratively with project team / Tech team in order to develop the most efficient design schemas;
Sit with developers to do pixel-perfect reviews of frontend products before they are pushed in production;
Consume our Design System library and contribute to its evolution.
Requirements:


Bachelor Degree in Creative Media / Interactive Design / Web Design / Web Development;
5+ years of experience building transactional website;
Specific experience in a fast growing ecommerce company;
Ability to solve problems of complexity through smart design;
Being data-driven, and be able to back up your assertions with data, with proficiency in analytic tools - Hotjar, Google Analytics, Optimizely etc;
A user-first attitude and ensure we consistently deliver a user-centric culture;
Strong understanding of web grids and browser limitations;
Familiarity with usability testing, A/B testing methods;
Proficiency with Photoshop, Adobe XD, Webflow, HTML, CSS, PHP;
Bouns: Experience with Shopify site designs / SDK.
Please include 2 URLs of your Open Source, personal projects into your resume.

Work location: Heritage Museum, Sha Tin
Working hours: 9am - 6pm (including 1-hour meal break), 5 days' workweek

Salary: $170 per hour (plus SH pay based on HK Labour Ordinance)
12 month's contract (renewable)

Scope of Works:
To render animation files to appropriate formats for presenting in different platforms;
To edit, retouch and manipulate digitized images for exhibition presentation and publicity uses;
To create 3D models of gallery plans by using modeling and rendering software;
To simulate immersive preview for gallery layout plans. To visualize and transform 2D graphical ideas into 3D graphics for exhibition presentation by applying appropriate textures and lighting effects to 31) models;
To keep in schedules and be responsible for printing/production process as well as to monitor the quality control of various outputs and delivery schedule;
To carry out instant back and forth checking of color tone against various color matching systems for output accuracy;
To archive all digital files upon completion of design works for record purpose and to compile different files to prepare exhibition portfolios;
Requirements:


Bachelor's Degree in design, preferably in visual communication, graphic design, exhibition design or multi-media design (full-time);
At least 5 years full-time relevant working experience in graphic, multi-media or exhibition design;
Experience in museums or cultural institutions is highly preferable;
 Proficiency in Macintosh Adobe Photoshop, Adobe illustrator, Adobe InDesign, Adobe After Effects, Adobe Premiere Pro, Sketchup Pro, Form7, 3DMax and Vectorworks etc.
Experience M desktop publishing;
Good command of Chinese and English;
Creative, self-motivated and with good communication skill;
Mature, able to work independently and under pressure;
